&lt;script src=&#34;https://vijay.eu/js/decibel-meter.js&#34;&gt;&lt;/script&gt;
&lt;link rel=&#34;stylesheet&#34; href=&#34;https://vijay.eu/css/decibel-meter.css&#34;&gt;
&lt;h3 id=&#34;details&#34;&gt;Details&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;p&gt;A simple browser-based decibel meter that uses your device&amp;rsquo;s microphone to measure sound levels. This tool provides a visual representation of ambient noise with corresponding descriptions of different noise levels.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h3 id=&#34;features&#34;&gt;Features&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Real-time sound level monitoring&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Speedometer-style visual indicator with needle and color-coded arcs&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;More granular voice level indicators for children&amp;rsquo;s voice modulation training&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Description of current noise level (whisper, indoor voice, classroom voice, etc.)&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Easy to use interface with start/stop button&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Color-coded legends with both standard and child-friendly voice level guidance&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;h3 id=&#34;technical-notes&#34;&gt;Technical Notes&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Uses the Web Audio API to access microphone data&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Provides approximate decibel measurements (calibration would be required for precise readings)&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Works best on desktop/mobile browsers with HTTPS or localhost (required for microphone access)&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;No data is stored or transmitted - all processing happens locally in your browser&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
